Members of the Bloomington Fire Department pick up hoses after putting out a fire in the 2400 block of S. Broadview Drive, Friday, June 7, 2019 in Bloomington, Ind. When firefighters arrived the house was smoking and flames were shooting out of the back of a house, and a second alarm was called. However, the firefighters put out the flames before the fire could spread more. The fire began before 6:45 p.m. (Photo by Jeremy Hogan/
The Bloomingtonian)
